            "id": "bbd0b0caf537486888aa8",
            "questionText": "A muon is created in the upper atmosphere at an altitude of 10,000 meters with a velocity of 0.99c relative to the Earth, and its proper half-life is $!$2.2\\times10^{-6}$!$ seconds. Considering an observer on Earth, calculate the probability that the muon will reach the Earth's surface without decaying. (Hint: First, compute the gamma factor ($!$\\gamma$!$) for the muon, then its dilated half-life as observed from Earth, and finally use the relation for the probability of not decaying after time t given by $!$e^{-t/(\\tau\\gamma)}$!$, where $!$\\tau$!$ is the proper half-life.)",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "706b9aa3d4cf4999b80ea",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying which formula is used to calculate the gamma factor ($!$\\gamma$!$) for an object moving at a relativistic speed. Choose the correct formula for $!$\\gamma$!$ from the options below.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "a0d65d2b-9a39-4a41-bda5-09be98a1c66a",
                        "79df688b-df1e-4c20-b8cc-247370a90937"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\gamma = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{1 - \\frac{v^2}{c^2}}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\gamma = \\sqrt{1 - \\frac{v^2}{c^2}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\gamma = \\frac{1}{1 - \\frac{v}{c}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "2c07056c708c4fb99405c",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that you've identified the formula, use it with $!$v = 0.99c$!$ to calculate the numerical value of the gamma factor. Provide your answer as a numerical value.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "7.09"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "a0d65d2b-9a39-4a41-bda5-09be98a1c66a",
                        "79df688b-df1e-4c20-b8cc-247370a90937"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "acba41019f9148a39b2b2",
                    "stepText": "Next, we need to account for time dilation. Identify the correct time dilation relation that connects the proper time (the muon\u2019s half-life in its rest frame) to the dilated time observed from Earth.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "0b935911-e793-4b1e-99f1-b6338367d9d5",
                        "a0d65d2b-9a39-4a41-bda5-09be98a1c66a"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$t_{dilated} = \\gamma \\, t_{proper}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$t_{dilated} = \\frac{t_{proper}}{\\gamma}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$t_{dilated} = t_{proper} + \\gamma$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
